<TITLE> Italian tourist, 3 of a family die in car crash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 30 (bdnews24.com)An Italian tourist and three of a familiy, all children, died, and another four were injured in a road accident on Dhaka-Sylhet Highway in Habiganj on Friday. Three of the dead children of Hamid Ali of Surma Tea Garden area in Madhabpur Upazila  Panna, 7, and Kalu Miah, 5, and Khadiza, 8. The Italian woman, who was named Francesca Maria, 35, died on way to hospital. Injured Chattu Mian, 35, of Talshahar village, Saidur Rahman, 45, of Netrakona, Rozia Khatun, 40, the wife of Hamid Ali, were admitted to Brahmanbaria Sadar Hospital. Officer in charge of Brahmanbaria Sadar Police Station Hamidul Islam said that Chattu Mian of Talshahar village of Ashuganj had been working for long in Italy. Chattu had recently come to Bangladesh with his wife and his Italian employer. Islam said the car they had been riding to go to Sylhet lost control, ran into a tree, then swerved to hit four passerbies before falling into a roadside ditch . Three passers-by died on the spot. bdnews
